CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 1, 1947, pg. 26, reads: "Good Prospect - Jackie Eisenberger, promising young Pittsburgh lightweight who seems to be going places in the fistic game. Since returning from the Army he has scored three knockouts in four fights and is now a main-eventer of the Aragon Gardens. He fights a main bout there on Feb. 6. Pictured with him is Jackie Griffith, his manager and once and outstanding battler in the local ring himself. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Boxer Jackie Eisenberger posed in corner of boxing ring with his manager, Jackie Griffith standing behind him, in gym with speed bag and tires in background
